1
00:01:54,800 --> 00:01:56,600
- Mr. Mills, how are you?
- I'm fine.

2
00:01:56,760 --> 00:01:57,760
- How are you?
- Fine.

3
00:01:57,920 --> 00:02:00,400
- I suppose you wanna see it again?
- Lf you don't mind.

4
00:02:00,880 --> 00:02:03,000
- You know where it is.
- Oh, yeah.

5
00:02:03,160 --> 00:02:06,440
If I charged you a dollar every time
you came to examine the machine...

6
00:02:06,600 --> 00:02:09,480
...you'd probably own it.
It's the one all the pros use.

7
00:02:09,640 --> 00:02:12,040
Mariah Carey. Beyoncé. Gwen Stefani.

8
00:02:12,240 --> 00:02:14,320
Really? Who's Beyoncé?

9
00:02:14,600 --> 00:02:16,920
Just kidding. I'll take it.

10
00:02:44,960 --> 00:02:47,240
Excuse me, sir.
The adult party's in the front.

11
00:02:47,400 --> 00:02:49,800
- I'm Kim's father.
- Excuse me, I work for her father.

12
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:52,960
- Her real father.
- It's okay, Cyril. I got it.

13
00:02:53,120 --> 00:02:55,120
- Hello, Bryan.
- Lenore.

14
00:02:56,800 --> 00:02:58,880
I just wanted to give Kim her present.

15
00:02:59,040 --> 00:03:00,840
We're letting the kids
have their space.

16
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:03,840
- Put it with the others.
- I wanna give it to her myself.

17
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:07,040
- Still having trouble following the rules.
- Oh, come on, Lennie.

18
00:03:07,200 --> 00:03:10,120
- I've asked you not to call me that.
- Excuse me. Lenore.

19
00:03:10,280 --> 00:03:11,680
- Dad!
- Oh, my darling.

20
00:03:11,880 --> 00:03:13,440
- Hi.
- Hello, my sweet.

21
00:03:13,800 --> 00:03:15,960
- Happy birthday.
- I was telling your father...

22
00:03:16,120 --> 00:03:18,600
...how we arranged the presents.
- Here.

23
00:03:18,760 --> 00:03:20,480
It's bad manners to open the one...

24
00:03:20,640 --> 00:03:22,440
...and not the others.
- Go on. Open it.

25
00:03:24,800 --> 00:03:26,880
- Cool.
- A karaoke machine?

26
00:03:27,040 --> 00:03:30,200
- Well, I figured she wants to be a singer.
- When she was 12, Bryan.

27
00:03:30,360 --> 00:03:32,720
- We've moved on.
- Thank you, Daddy.

28
00:03:32,880 --> 00:03:34,440
My pleasure.

29
00:03:34,640 --> 00:03:37,560
- I still wanna be a singer. Don't tell Mom.
- You got it.

30
00:03:37,720 --> 00:03:39,400
Here. One for the book.

31
00:03:39,600 --> 00:03:42,280
- We have a professional photographer.
- Big smile, sweetie.

32
00:03:42,840 --> 00:03:44,760
That's my girl.

33
00:03:51,600 --> 00:03:54,360
Oh, my God. Oh, my God!

34
00:03:54,520 --> 00:03:56,200
Oh, my God! Oh, my God!
Oh, my God!

35
00:03:56,400 --> 00:03:57,600
Oh, my... Stuart!

36
00:03:58,160 --> 00:04:00,200
Stuart, I love you! I love you!
I love you!

37
00:04:00,400 --> 00:04:02,120
Happy birthday, sweetie.

38
00:04:12,600 --> 00:04:16,160
- Oh, Stuart, you're impossible.
- I know.

39
00:04:16,320 --> 00:04:17,880
- Hey, Bryan.
- Stuart.

40
00:04:18,480 --> 00:04:21,560
- She's not a little girl anymore, huh?
- I guess not.

41
00:04:21,720 --> 00:04:24,840
- Will you join us for lunch?
- No, thanks.

42
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:27,840
I just wanted to be here
to wish her a happy birthday.

43
00:04:28,400 --> 00:04:30,920
- Good to see you, Bryan.
- You too.

44
00:04:44,760 --> 00:04:46,160
Thanks.

45
00:05:21,400 --> 00:05:22,440
- Hey.
- Hey.

46
00:05:23,680 --> 00:05:25,160
You forgot.

47
00:05:26,040 --> 00:05:27,040
Come on in.

48
00:05:27,200 --> 00:05:30,360
It's not like I didn't call to remind you.
Third Saturday in May?

49
00:05:30,520 --> 00:05:33,880
- Red meat, red wine? Sound familiar?
- He probably had a lot on his mind.

50
00:05:34,040 --> 00:05:37,000
Yeah, the busy life of a retiree.
Every day a new adventure.

51
00:05:37,200 --> 00:05:40,480
What does a retiree do, anyway?
Take naps? Play golf?

52
00:05:40,640 --> 00:05:43,040
- Hit on rich widows?
- That takes care of the morning.

53
00:05:43,200 --> 00:05:45,600
Yeah, well, come on, guys.
You know why I'm here.

54
00:05:45,760 --> 00:05:47,240
Yeah, how's that going?

55
00:05:47,440 --> 00:05:49,160
Okay. We had her birthday today.

56
00:05:49,360 --> 00:05:50,800
Can you believe my Kimmy's 17?

57
00:05:51,920 --> 00:05:53,640
Seventeen?

58
00:05:54,480 --> 00:05:57,200
- To Kim.
- Lennie still got a hard-on for you?

59
00:05:58,000 --> 00:06:00,200
She's not Lennie anymore.
She's Lenore.

60
00:06:00,400 --> 00:06:01,920
Oh, she's still got a hard-on.

61
00:06:02,080 --> 00:06:04,400
- And the husband?
- The same. Perfect.

62
00:06:04,560 --> 00:06:08,040
- Dig deep enough, there's always shit.
- We can dig if you want us to dig.

63
00:06:08,200 --> 00:06:10,360
What, you think he hasn't
done it already?

64
00:06:10,520 --> 00:06:11,720
Thank you, Bernie.

65
00:06:11,880 --> 00:06:14,640
- How's Kimmy?
- Good. She's good.

66
00:06:14,800 --> 00:06:16,840
Yeah? She sleep over yet?

67
00:06:17,040 --> 00:06:19,400
Well, let's say we're working on it.

68
00:06:19,920 --> 00:06:23,000
She appreciate the fact
that you've given up your life...

69
00:06:23,160 --> 00:06:25,440
...in order to be closer to her?

70
00:06:25,920 --> 00:06:27,560
What a life, huh?

71
00:06:28,120 --> 00:06:30,560
Hey, remember Beirut
after the chief disappeared?

72
00:06:30,720 --> 00:06:33,160
Bry was in deep with that
crazy sheik from Hezbollah?

73
00:06:33,360 --> 00:06:35,560
The guy said he'd get us inside
then disappeared.

74
00:06:35,760 --> 00:06:37,560
We're scrambling to get the hell out...

75
00:06:37,720 --> 00:06:39,840
...before we get taken down
and where are you?

76
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:41,800
I promised never to miss her birthday.

77
00:06:41,960 --> 00:06:43,960
Yeah, that went down well
at Langley...

78
00:06:44,120 --> 00:06:46,120
...when they found out
you flew the coop...

79
00:06:46,320 --> 00:06:49,000
...to attend your child's birthday
9000 miles away.

80
00:06:49,200 --> 00:06:51,000
Where did you say
your next posting was?

81
00:06:51,160 --> 00:06:53,800
The Arctic Circle spying on penguins,
I believe it was.

82
00:06:53,960 --> 00:06:55,560
No, penguins live in Antarctica.

83
00:06:55,720 --> 00:06:58,080
Actually, it was Alaska.
What's your point, Sam?

84
00:06:58,240 --> 00:07:02,480
My point is we have an open space.
Say the word, it's yours.

85
00:07:04,400 --> 00:07:06,040
Who likes theirs rare?

86
00:07:06,760 --> 00:07:07,840
- Guys.
- See you, Bryan.

87
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:10,120
- Good night, guys.
- See you, Bry.

88
00:07:10,320 --> 00:07:12,320
Hey, look, look, look.
All kidding aside...

89
00:07:12,480 --> 00:07:15,480
...it's a great thing trying to make up
for lost time with Kimmy.

90
00:07:15,640 --> 00:07:17,440
But tomorrow's job? Right here.

91
00:07:17,600 --> 00:07:19,160
Four hours' work, 2500 bucks...

92
00:07:19,320 --> 00:07:22,200
...just for taking some pop diva
to and from her concert.

93
00:07:22,360 --> 00:07:23,800
- We're one short.
- A singer?

94
00:07:23,960 --> 00:07:26,880
I don't know if you'd call her a singer.
More like a cash cow.

95
00:07:27,040 --> 00:07:29,840
Twenty million records sold already
and she's not even 25.

96
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:31,200
Job's a piece of cake.

97
00:07:31,360 --> 00:07:34,400
We get her there and back.
Inside, they've got their own people.

98
00:07:34,560 --> 00:07:36,600
- Okay.
- Okay. Okay?

99
00:07:36,760 --> 00:07:37,800
- Yeah.
- Like that's it?

100
00:07:37,960 --> 00:07:39,080
Yeah.

101
00:07:39,280 --> 00:07:42,880
- It'll be perfect. Just like old times.
- Better. No one gets killed.

102
00:07:43,600 --> 00:07:46,360
- Tomorrow. Good night, guys.
- See you.

103
00:07:46,520 --> 00:07:49,720
- Get in the back, Wendy.
- I always get in the back.

104
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:18,440
Ma'am, if you don't mind,
I suggest you keep moving.

105
00:08:18,600 --> 00:08:20,600
My mother is ma'am,
if you don't mind.

106
00:08:24,040 --> 00:08:26,680
- Come on, it's time now. Let's go.
- Okay.

107
00:08:28,040 --> 00:08:30,760
Bernie, Casey, you're out here.
Bry, you're in the room.

108
00:08:30,920 --> 00:08:32,440
Okay.

109
00:08:33,280 --> 00:08:36,120
Let's go, let's go, let's go.

110
00:08:36,280 --> 00:08:38,040
Thank you for coming.

111
00:08:51,280 --> 00:08:53,440
Wow, it was beautiful.

112
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:56,480
Thanks. What did you say
your name was again?

113
00:08:56,640 --> 00:08:58,120
Mills. Bryan Mills.

114
00:08:58,320 --> 00:09:00,880
- Nice to meet you, Bryan Mills.
- You too.

115
00:09:01,800 --> 00:09:04,800
- You're on. Come on, let's go now.
- Okay, guys.

116
00:09:04,960 --> 00:09:05,960
Excuse me, miss.

117
00:09:06,120 --> 00:09:10,400
I've a daughter who wants to be a singer
and was wondering if you had any tips.

118
00:09:11,560 --> 00:09:13,080
Yeah, I do.

119
00:09:13,240 --> 00:09:15,320
Tell her to pick another career.

120
00:09:18,080 --> 00:09:20,280
I got one.
We're waiting on an air strike...

121
00:09:20,440 --> 00:09:23,200
...and we're waiting
and then my satellite phone rings.

122
00:09:23,360 --> 00:09:24,360
- Who is it?
- Hello?

123
00:09:24,520 --> 00:09:26,240
- The guy we're to terminate.
- Honey.

124
00:09:26,400 --> 00:09:29,320
- He'd like to know if we want some tea.
- Sorry, guys, it's Kim.

125
00:09:31,120 --> 00:09:32,680
The noise?

126
00:09:32,880 --> 00:09:34,880
I'm at a concert.

127
00:09:35,480 --> 00:09:37,960
You know this song? Yeah?

128
00:09:38,120 --> 00:09:41,160
Yep, that's her.
No, no, no, I'm not attending.

129
00:09:41,320 --> 00:09:42,720
I'm... I'm not attending.

130
00:09:42,880 --> 00:09:45,400
I'm helping some friends out
with security.

131
00:09:45,560 --> 00:09:47,520
Well, of course I met her.

132
00:09:47,680 --> 00:09:49,280
Who do you think's guarding her?

133
00:09:49,440 --> 00:09:51,520
I'm glad you're impressed.

134
00:09:51,680 --> 00:09:53,800
Hey, I'm happy you called.

135
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:57,120
I'm happy you called. What?

136
00:09:57,280 --> 00:09:59,520
Lunch? Tomorrow?

137
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:03,160
Sure, sure. I know the place.

138
00:10:03,320 --> 00:10:05,480
Twelve-thirty it is.

139
00:10:06,040 --> 00:10:07,520
I'll see you then.

140
00:10:08,040 --> 00:10:09,800
- Here he is. And...?
- What happened?

141
00:10:09,960 --> 00:10:11,720
- She wants to have lunch.
- Okay.

142
00:10:11,880 --> 00:10:13,960
- Just the two of us.
- All right. Fantastic.

143
00:10:14,160 --> 00:10:15,840
See? There's progress. That's great.

144
00:10:29,000 --> 00:10:32,040
Who left that gate open?
Bry, get her out of here. Take the lead.

145
00:10:32,240 --> 00:10:33,280
- Move!
- Go, go!

146
00:10:35,600 --> 00:10:36,840
More security here now!

147
00:10:37,040 --> 00:10:38,600
That's it. Move.

148
00:10:44,960 --> 00:10:46,760
Casey!

149
00:10:48,600 --> 00:10:50,400
Bernie, stand by, stand by.

150
00:10:50,560 --> 00:10:52,520
- Go, go, go.
- Watch your head.

151
00:10:56,520 --> 00:10:59,800
Here, take this. The sugar will
take the edge off the shock.

152
00:10:59,960 --> 00:11:02,120
Come on, come on, drink some more.

153
00:11:10,960 --> 00:11:12,680
It's okay. It's okay. You're safe.

154
00:11:18,360 --> 00:11:19,880
You're safe now.

155
00:11:22,200 --> 00:11:23,400
Bernie.

156
00:11:23,560 --> 00:11:25,440
Casey. Rambo.

157
00:11:26,360 --> 00:11:28,840
Seriously, Bry,
you should think about coming with us.

158
00:11:29,000 --> 00:11:31,480
You've got the edge.
There's more of this to be had.

159
00:11:31,640 --> 00:11:33,480
- She's going to college next year?
- Yep.

160
00:11:33,640 --> 00:11:36,600
- You're gonna lose her.
- That gives me a year to find her.

161
00:11:37,320 --> 00:11:40,040
Mr. Mills, she'd like to see you.

162
00:11:45,120 --> 00:11:47,800
- How are you feeling?
- Better.

163
00:11:50,440 --> 00:11:52,200
So your daughter
wants to be a singer?

164
00:11:53,760 --> 00:11:55,360
Yep, since she was 5.

165
00:11:55,520 --> 00:11:57,240
It's not what everyone thinks it is.

166
00:11:57,400 --> 00:12:02,400
Once the glam wears off, it's just
a lot of hotel rooms, lots of airports.

167
00:12:02,920 --> 00:12:04,000
It's what she wants.

168
00:12:07,880 --> 00:12:09,960
The first number is Gio,
my vocal coach.

169
00:12:10,120 --> 00:12:12,040
If he says she can sing, she can sing.

170
00:12:12,200 --> 00:12:14,680
He'll give her coaching she needs,
the fee is on me.

171
00:12:14,840 --> 00:12:16,720
The second number is my manager.

172
00:12:16,880 --> 00:12:19,360
If Gio clears her,
he'll make sure she gets a shot.

173
00:12:21,240 --> 00:12:25,400
- Thank you.
- No, Mr. Mills, thank you.

174
00:12:41,080 --> 00:12:43,160
- There she is.
- Dad.

175
00:12:46,120 --> 00:12:47,920
- Hi, sweetie.
- Hey.

176
00:12:48,440 --> 00:12:50,240
- Hi.
- Hi.

177
00:12:50,400 --> 00:12:51,760
Don't look so excited.

178
00:12:51,920 --> 00:12:55,200
I was just surprised.
I thought it was just gonna be Kim and I.

179
00:12:55,720 --> 00:12:56,920
I asked Mom to come.

180
00:12:58,880 --> 00:13:02,440
One raspberry-banana milkshake,
extra cherries, just the way you like it.

181
00:13:02,640 --> 00:13:04,000
- Thanks.
- Lennie... Lenore.

182
00:13:04,160 --> 00:13:06,760
- Would you like something?
- I'm fine, thanks.

183
00:13:07,240 --> 00:13:08,680
So?

184
00:13:09,240 --> 00:13:10,640
So, Dad, guess what.

185
00:13:10,800 --> 00:13:12,360
- You know my friend Amanda?
- Yep.

186
00:13:13,160 --> 00:13:16,040
Her cousins asked us to spend vacation
with them in Paris.

187
00:13:16,240 --> 00:13:17,240
How cool is that?

188
00:13:17,400 --> 00:13:19,840
- Why do you want to go to Paris?
- Dad. Hello?

189
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:23,160
The Louvre, the lmpressionist museum,
the Picasso Museum.

190
00:13:23,320 --> 00:13:25,120
I didn't know you were so into art.

191
00:13:25,280 --> 00:13:28,200
Are you kidding? I've been to the MOMA,
like, a hundred times.

192
00:13:28,360 --> 00:13:32,920
Amanda went last summer, she came
back, she could practically speak French.

193
00:13:35,240 --> 00:13:36,640
And because you're under 18...

194
00:13:36,800 --> 00:13:39,520
...you need my permission
to leave the country?

195
00:13:40,080 --> 00:13:43,360
Dad, please. I really, really wanna go.

196
00:13:43,520 --> 00:13:46,240
They've got this
sick apartment overlooking the river.

197
00:13:46,400 --> 00:13:48,760
- Just you and Amanda?
- And her cousins.

198
00:13:48,920 --> 00:13:52,040
Don't make a big deal out of this, Bryan.
Just sign the paper.

199
00:13:57,160 --> 00:13:59,200
- What?
- I'm not comfortable with this.

200
00:13:59,360 --> 00:14:01,000
- Dad.
- I know the world, sweetie.

201
00:14:01,600 --> 00:14:04,200
- Dad, please.
- A 17-year-old should not travel alone.

202
00:14:04,400 --> 00:14:06,520
- I'm not gonna be alone.
- Two 17-year-olds.

203
00:14:06,680 --> 00:14:08,600
Amanda's 19.

204
00:14:13,960 --> 00:14:16,360
How about this?
How about if I go along?

205
00:14:16,560 --> 00:14:19,240
You won't know I'm there.
I'm very good at being invisible.

206
00:14:19,440 --> 00:14:22,600
As you so amply demonstrated
for most of her life.

207
00:14:22,760 --> 00:14:24,280
Just sign the paper, Bryan.

208
00:14:27,440 --> 00:14:28,520
I'll think about it.

209
00:14:28,680 --> 00:14:30,760
Everyone at this table
knows what that means.

210
00:14:31,720 --> 00:14:34,080
Hey, Kimmy, there's something else.

211
00:14:34,840 --> 00:14:37,240
- I don't want anything else.
- Kim.

212
00:14:43,600 --> 00:14:44,840
- I don't get you.
- What?

213
00:14:45,520 --> 00:14:48,200
You sacrificed our marriage
in the service of the country.

214
00:14:48,360 --> 00:14:51,000
You made a mess of your life
in service of your country.

215
00:14:51,160 --> 00:14:53,880
Can't you sacrifice a little
this time for your daughter?

216
00:14:54,040 --> 00:14:56,800
- I would sacrifice anything for her.
- What's your problem?

217
00:14:56,960 --> 00:15:00,120
I'm not comfortable
putting my daughter at risk.

218
00:15:00,480 --> 00:15:04,120
Putting our daughter at risk
by going to Paris?

219
00:15:04,440 --> 00:15:06,440
You're pathetic.

220
00:15:21,240 --> 00:15:23,920
- She's coming.
- Thanks.

221
00:15:27,040 --> 00:15:28,040
Three conditions.

222
00:15:28,360 --> 00:15:30,920
The address and phone number
of where you're staying.

223
00:15:31,080 --> 00:15:33,920
You move, I wanna know where
and with whom you'll be staying.

224
00:15:34,080 --> 00:15:37,480
Call me when you land. Call me
every night before you go to sleep.

225
00:15:37,680 --> 00:15:39,360
It's international. My number is in.

226
00:15:39,520 --> 00:15:41,560
- Okay, awesome.
- Kimmy, you're not focused.

227
00:15:41,720 --> 00:15:42,920
- I am.
- What did I say?

228
00:15:43,120 --> 00:15:46,280
You said call you when I land,
every night before I go to sleep...

229
00:15:46,480 --> 00:15:49,160
...your phone's international,
the number's programmed in.

230
00:15:49,360 --> 00:15:52,360
Okay, one last thing.
I get to take you to the airport.

231
00:15:52,560 --> 00:15:53,960
Okay.

232
00:15:54,880 --> 00:15:56,640
- There you go.
- Yes.

233
00:15:56,800 --> 00:16:00,000
Thank you, Daddy.
Thank you, thank you, thank you.

234
00:16:00,160 --> 00:16:01,800
Mom!

235
00:16:03,760 --> 00:16:04,760
I love you, Dad.

236
00:16:05,560 --> 00:16:08,800
Mom, he signed it, he signed it.
I'm gonna go call Amanda!

237
00:16:12,440 --> 00:16:15,040
Wouldn't it have been easier
to sign the first time?

238
00:16:15,200 --> 00:16:18,680
Wouldn't it have been easier
if you and I had talked about it first?

239
00:16:22,600 --> 00:16:25,560
