01:03:18,200 --> 01:03:22,000
Now, I don't have any more time
to waste, Marko from Tropoja.

722
01:03:22,440 --> 01:03:24,640
Give me what I need
or this switch'll stay on...

723
01:03:24,800 --> 01:03:27,640
...till they turn power off
for lack of payment on the bill.

724
01:03:28,840 --> 01:03:30,080
Where is my daughter?

725
01:03:30,600 --> 01:03:33,880
We don't keep virgins, we sell them.

726
01:03:34,120 --> 01:03:36,160
She was virgin, lot of money.

727
01:03:36,360 --> 01:03:38,400
You sold my daughter? You sold her?

728
01:03:40,360 --> 01:03:41,920
To who?

729
01:03:42,600 --> 01:03:44,160
I don't know.

730
01:03:46,520 --> 01:03:48,320
- What?
- Saint-Clair.

731
01:03:48,800 --> 01:03:49,760
Saint-Clair.

732
01:03:50,200 --> 01:03:52,640
Saint-Clair? Saint-Clair.
Is that a person, a place?

733
01:03:54,200 --> 01:03:57,080
Person. Patrice Saint-Clair.

734
01:03:57,280 --> 01:03:58,240
Patrice Saint-Clair.

735
01:03:59,400 --> 01:04:00,640
Where can I find him?

736
01:04:01,600 --> 01:04:03,360
I don't know, I don't know.

737
01:04:04,120 --> 01:04:06,720
I don't know. I don't know.
I don't know.

738
01:04:06,920 --> 01:04:09,080
Please! I don't know!

739
01:04:09,240 --> 01:04:13,080
I don't know! No! Please! Please.

740
01:04:13,240 --> 01:04:15,000
Please.

741
01:04:15,160 --> 01:04:17,160
Not that. Please.

742
01:04:17,320 --> 01:04:18,680
I believe you.

743
01:04:21,400 --> 01:04:23,560
But it's not gonna save you.

744
01:04:37,800 --> 01:04:40,360
- I'm home
- Daddy!

745
01:04:41,000 --> 01:04:43,920
- Good evening my loves
- Daddy

746
01:04:44,360 --> 01:04:46,600
The chicken smells good
I can smell it from the street!

747
01:04:45,800 --> 01:04:47,560
Look who dropped by.

748
01:04:48,360 --> 01:04:50,840
Bryan, what a pleasant surprise.

749
01:04:51,040 --> 01:04:52,000
Jean-Claude.

750
01:04:52,200 --> 01:04:54,560
The children waited up for you.

751
01:04:54,720 --> 01:04:57,920
If you tuck them in, maybe we can eat
before everything gets cold.

752
01:04:58,080 --> 01:04:59,520
Bryan, will you do the honors?

753
01:04:59,720 --> 01:05:01,560
- Sure.
- I'll be just a minute.

754
01:05:02,000 --> 01:05:05,400
- Children, bed time
- Oh...
- Thank you

755
01:05:30,840 --> 01:05:32,920
I was just telling Bryan
how nice it's been...

756
01:05:33,080 --> 01:05:35,160
...since you left the old job
for the new one.

757
01:05:35,320 --> 01:05:38,040
Home every night for dinner,
get to see the kids more.

758
01:05:38,200 --> 01:05:41,120
Yeah, must be nice coming home
every night, seeing your kids.

759
01:05:41,320 --> 01:05:43,320
Bryan has been thinking
about relocating.

760
01:05:43,720 --> 01:05:45,120
- Really?
- Yes.

761
01:05:45,320 --> 01:05:47,040
To Paris, he's been visiting houses.

762
01:05:47,200 --> 01:05:49,760
- White or dark meat?
- Dark, please.

763
01:05:49,920 --> 01:05:51,200
Find anything interesting?

764
01:05:51,360 --> 01:05:55,000
As a matter of fact, I did, in the 10th
arrondissement on Rue Paradis.

765
01:05:55,880 --> 01:05:58,240
People there know someone
that works in your office.

766
01:05:58,480 --> 01:06:00,360
A Mr. Macon. Do you know him?

767
01:06:00,520 --> 01:06:02,720
Oh, Henry. I call him Mr. Nervous.

768
01:06:02,880 --> 01:06:06,400
Always seems like he's about to
have a problem. Carrots?

769
01:06:06,600 --> 01:06:08,320
I got to the bottom of it,
Jean-Claude.

770
01:06:08,680 --> 01:06:09,760
I know everything.

771
01:06:10,480 --> 01:06:12,640
I hope you're not involved in this shit.

772
01:06:13,960 --> 01:06:16,680
- What shit?
- This is not the time or place, Bryan.

773
01:06:16,840 --> 01:06:18,840
- Are you involved?
- Involved in what?

774
01:06:19,480 --> 01:06:20,920
What are you two talking about?

775
01:06:21,080 --> 01:06:24,520
- Are you?
- My salary is X, my expenses are Y.

776
01:06:24,680 --> 01:06:26,680
As long as my family is provided for...

777
01:06:26,840 --> 01:06:29,320
...I do not care
where the difference comes from.

778
01:06:29,480 --> 01:06:31,320
That is my entire involvement.

779
01:06:31,480 --> 01:06:33,400
- What about my family?
- I told you...

780
01:06:33,560 --> 01:06:35,880
...I would help
as long as it didn't cause trouble.

781
01:06:36,040 --> 01:06:37,320
Who is Patrice Saint-Clair?

782
01:06:37,480 --> 01:06:40,840
I don't know, I don't care.
I am driving you to the airport.

783
01:06:41,080 --> 01:06:42,240
Jean-Claude.

784
01:06:43,680 --> 01:06:45,280
Let's get going. Dinner is over.

785
01:06:45,440 --> 01:06:47,160
- I'm not finished yet.
- Yes, you are.

786
01:06:47,400 --> 01:06:50,120
- No!
- No, I'm not.

787
01:06:54,680 --> 01:06:57,760
That's what happens when you sit
behind a desk. You forget things.

788
01:06:57,960 --> 01:07:00,320
Like the weight in the hand
of a gun that's loaded.

789
01:07:02,320 --> 01:07:03,400
Isabelle!

790
01:07:04,800 --> 01:07:05,920
It's a flesh wound.

791
01:07:06,080 --> 01:07:09,600
But if you don't get me what I need,
the last thing you'll see...

792
01:07:09,800 --> 01:07:11,680
...is the bullet
I put between her eyes.

793
01:07:11,880 --> 01:07:14,800
Now, Patrice Saint-Clair.

794
01:07:25,960 --> 01:07:27,680
You could've made this
less painful...

795
01:07:27,840 --> 01:07:31,800
...if you had been more concerned about
my daughter and less about your desk.

796
01:07:31,960 --> 01:07:34,200
Please apologize to your wife for me.

797
01:08:36,800 --> 01:08:39,520
- Can I help you?
- Yes, I'm here to see Mr. Saint-Clair.

798
01:08:39,720 --> 01:08:41,200
Your name, please.

799
01:08:45,040 --> 01:08:46,880
I'm sorry,
your name is not on the list.

800
01:08:47,040 --> 01:08:48,520
Oh, please check again.

801
01:08:51,480 --> 01:08:53,120
Inside.

802
01:09:38,800 --> 01:09:40,000
May I help you, sir?

803
01:09:45,400 --> 01:09:47,800
- Your champagne.
- Yeah, I will take it.

804
01:09:57,160 --> 01:10:00,320
<i>I have 50,000. Fifty thousand.</i>

805
01:10:02,040 --> 01:10:03,960
<i>Fifty thousand.</i>

806
01:10:05,480 --> 01:10:08,600
<i>One hundred, 100,000.</i>

807
01:10:10,360 --> 01:10:13,400
<i>One hundred, 150.</i>

808
01:10:14,440 --> 01:10:15,560
<i>I have 150.</i>

809
01:10:16,200 --> 01:10:18,240
Your champagne, sir.

810
01:10:19,000 --> 01:10:21,600
<i>Two, I have two, 250.</i>

811
01:10:21,760 --> 01:10:22,720
May I serve?

812
01:10:22,920 --> 01:10:24,200
<i>- Please.
- I have 250.</i>

813
01:10:25,960 --> 01:10:27,640
<i>Two-fifty.</i>

814
01:10:28,200 --> 01:10:31,120
<i>Sold for 250,000.</i>

815
01:10:39,000 --> 01:10:43,000
You want me to bid?
There is one left.

816
01:10:43,400 --> 01:10:45,000
We'll see in a moment.

817
01:10:48,440 --> 01:10:50,520
<i>The last item.</i>

818
01:10:50,840 --> 01:10:53,240
<i>As usual, we save the best for last.</i>

819
01:10:53,560 --> 01:10:55,640
<i>Speaks English, some French.</i>

820
01:10:55,800 --> 01:10:57,160
<i>Certified pure.</i>

821
01:11:06,720 --> 01:11:07,680
- Sorry.
- Get out.

822
01:11:09,240 --> 01:11:11,840
<i>The bidding will begin at 100,000.</i>

823
01:11:15,200 --> 01:11:17,240
<i>One hundred.</i>

824
01:11:26,760 --> 01:11:28,480
<i>One hundred thousand.</i>

825
01:11:28,680 --> 01:11:30,720
- I said...
- I heard what you said.

826
01:11:30,920 --> 01:11:32,160
Buy her.

827
01:11:32,360 --> 01:11:33,400
<i>I have 100.</i>

828
01:11:35,080 --> 01:11:37,760
<i>- Buy her.
- One-fifty.</i>

829
01:11:37,920 --> 01:11:39,400
<i>Two hundred.</i>

830
01:11:40,120 --> 01:11:42,680
<i>Two-fifty, three, 350.</i>

831
01:11:42,880 --> 01:11:46,000
<i>Three hundred and fifty thousand.</i>

832
01:11:46,560 --> 01:11:48,680
<i>Four. Four.</i>

833
01:11:49,160 --> 01:11:51,520
<i>Four-fifty, 450.</i>

834
01:11:51,760 --> 01:11:53,560
<i>Four hundred and fifty thousand.</i>

835
01:11:54,240 --> 01:11:55,240
<i>Four-fifty.</i>

836
01:11:56,360 --> 01:11:58,280
<i>Five hundred. Five hundred thousand.</i>

837
01:11:58,440 --> 01:12:02,240
<i>Five hundred thousand. Sold.</i>

838
01:12:02,720 --> 01:12:06,240
<i>That concludes the sales for tonight.
Thank you all for coming.</i>

839
01:12:06,720 --> 01:12:09,560
<i>- You can collect your purchases directly.
- Move.</i>

840
01:12:09,720 --> 01:12:13,560
- You will never get away with this.
- Lf you wanna live, you'll make sure I do.

841
01:12:23,000 --> 01:12:25,360
Now, Mr...?

842
01:12:31,320 --> 01:12:34,600
Well, we know you're not this man.
So, what do we call you?

843
01:12:37,800 --> 01:12:39,640
It doesn't matter what we call you...

844
01:12:39,800 --> 01:12:42,160
...what does matter
is what you're doing here.

845
01:12:43,480 --> 01:12:45,320
The last girl, I'm her father.

846
01:12:47,800 --> 01:12:50,800
- Oh, my.
- Give her to me.

847
01:12:52,040 --> 01:12:54,240
I wish I could, honestly.

848
01:12:54,400 --> 01:12:56,000
See, I'm a father myself.

849
01:12:56,200 --> 01:12:58,120
I have two sons and a daughter...

850
01:12:58,280 --> 01:13:01,160
...but let me tell you something,
Mr. Whoever-You-Are.

851
01:13:01,360 --> 01:13:02,600
This is a business.

852
01:13:02,800 --> 01:13:04,480
This is a very unique business...

853
01:13:04,640 --> 01:13:07,240
...with a very unique clientele.
- I'll pay.

854
01:13:07,480 --> 01:13:09,800
In this business,
you have no refunds, returns...

855
01:13:10,000 --> 01:13:11,960
...discounts, buybacks.
All sales are final.

856
01:13:12,160 --> 01:13:16,800
Besides discretion,
it's about the only rule we have.

857
01:13:18,680 --> 01:13:21,080
Kill him. Quietly. I have guests.

858
01:14:16,920 --> 01:14:19,200
Would you please go see
which part of "quietly"...

859
01:14:19,360 --> 01:14:21,920
...they did not understand?
- Yes, sir.

860
01:14:40,360 --> 01:14:43,960
Okay, we can resolve this.
I know how you feel.

861
01:14:44,120 --> 01:14:46,680
We should talk, okay?
We can work this out.

862
01:14:48,880 --> 01:14:50,520
You have no idea...

863
01:14:51,560 --> 01:14:52,760
- Where is she?
- Please.

864
01:14:52,960 --> 01:14:54,160
Understand. Please try...

865
01:14:58,680 --> 01:15:01,600
There's a boat by the quay.

866
01:15:02,800 --> 01:15:04,200
Please understand.

867
01:15:04,360 --> 01:15:08,560
It was all business,
it wasn't personal.

868
01:15:08,760 --> 01:15:10,400
It was all personal to me.

869
01:17:50,480 --> 01:17:52,360
It's ready

870
01:18:50,280 --> 01:18:52,080
You - take the girls

871
01:18:53,000 --> 01:18:54,400
You - follow me

872
01:18:55,140 --> 01:18:56,400
Invaders!  Search the boat.

873
01:19:33,860 --> 01:19:36,080
Where are you?

874
01:19:37,440 --> 01:19:38,460
Why are you not answering?

875
01:20:03,920 --> 01:20:05,080
Get inside!

876
01:20:05,960 --> 01:20:06,960
What's the problem?

877
01:20:07,140 --> 01:20:09,200
The girls father has arrived.

878
01:20:09,440 --> 01:20:10,260
Leave it to me.

879
01:21:50,400 --> 01:21:51,400
We can...

880
01:22:02,880 --> 01:22:06,440
- Daddy.
- Kim.

881
01:22:07,200 --> 01:22:09,240
You came for me.

882
01:22:13,600 --> 01:22:15,040
You came for me.

883
01:22:17,680 --> 01:22:19,640
I told you I would.

884
01:22:47,440 --> 01:22:50,440
<i>May I have your attention.
If you're waiting for oversized bags...</i>

885
01:22:51,880 --> 01:22:53,720
Mom.

886
01:22:55,360 --> 01:22:57,280
Oh, my God.

887
01:22:57,640 --> 01:22:59,840
Oh, sweetie.

888
01:23:00,480 --> 01:23:02,720
Oh, here, let me get that for you.

889
01:23:02,880 --> 01:23:04,720
Bryan, if there's anything you need...

890
01:23:06,040 --> 01:23:08,120
I've got everything I need.

891
01:23:08,280 --> 01:23:10,760
I love you so much.

892
01:23:12,840 --> 01:23:14,840
Stuart.

893
01:23:15,720 --> 01:23:17,600
Thank you.

894
01:23:24,600 --> 01:23:27,400
<i>Attention, travelers.
You are not required to...</i>

895
01:23:27,560 --> 01:23:29,440
Shall we go?

896
01:23:34,240 --> 01:23:36,640
Sure you don't wanna ride with us?

897
01:23:37,240 --> 01:23:41,680
- I'll be fine. I'll take a cab. Thanks.
- All right.

898
01:23:49,640 --> 01:23:51,760
- I love you, Dad.
- Love you too.

899
01:24:13,920 --> 01:24:16,800
- Where are we?
- I told you. It's a surprise.

900
01:24:18,680 --> 01:24:20,560
- Hi.
- Hi.

901
01:24:23,360 --> 01:24:26,680
When someone says "Hi,"
it's usually polite to say "Hi" back.

902
01:24:27,400 --> 01:24:28,440
Hi.

903
01:24:28,640 --> 01:24:30,040
I heard you wanna be a singer.

904
01:24:30,200 --> 01:24:31,880
- I do.
- She does.

905
01:24:33,440 --> 01:24:36,640
Well, come on in.
Let's see what you got.

